eq0$ ,so $\mathbf{w}=\mathbf{x}*\mathbf{z}$ is nonzero and orthogonal to x and z. However, if $(\mathbf{x}*\mathbf{x})	imes\mathbf{y}
eq0$ then $\mathbf{w}=\mathbf{x}*(\mathbf{x}*\mathbf{y})=(\mathbf{x}*\mathbf{x})*\mathbf{y}=(\mathbf{x}*\mathbf{x})	imes\mathbf{y}$ is also orthogonal to y, a contradiction.
